President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived in Lagos on a working visit to commission and inspect some projects in the state. His aircraft reportedly touched down at about 10am on Tuesday at the Presidential Wing of the Murtala Muhammed Airport, Lagos. Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu and some members of the Lagos State Executive Council welcome the President to the state. Also Read: Lagos State Announces Diversion Of Traffic Ahead Of President Buhari’s Visit Today He later boarded a chopper to Lekki, where he is expected to commission the multi-billion dollars Dangote Fertiliser Plant. President Buhari is also expected to inspect the ongoing construction at the Dangote Refinery, as well as the Lekki Deep Sea Port.